  "bio": "<p>Meet Cayden. He’s a kid who has faced more challenges before turning ten than most people do in a lifetime, yet he still manages to show up with a smile. Cayden was born with congenital scoliosis, and from the start, life gave him a lot to handle. He’s had multiple surgeries and even lost one of his legs. Through it all, Cayden kept going, always resilient, hopeful, and full of heart. </p><p>But then, something happened that no one expected. During a spinal fusion surgery meant to&nbsp;improve&nbsp;his quality of life, Cayden suffered a stroke that left him paralyzed from the waist down. He spent 11 weeks in the hospital, fighting through pain, infections, and more surgeries, and not once did he give up. Simply put, Cayden is a force.</p><p>Cayden deserved a space that matched his spirit, so that’s exactly what we set out to build.Thanks to the incredible generosity of&nbsp;Jackson Healthcare,&nbsp;a loyal partner and champion of our mission, Sunshine on a Ranney Day was able to give Cayden a fully accessible bathroom designed just for him. And when we say&nbsp;just for him, we mean it: the whole space is decorated in Pittsburgh Steelers style, because that’s Cayden’s world, and we were just designing in it.</p><p>The vision came to life thanks to&nbsp;B Noelle Design, who donated their time and talent to make every detail count, from the color scheme to the finishing touches. It’s not just functional. It’s Cayden.</p><p>A transformation like this takes a village, and we are so grateful for ours. Because of all of you, Cayden now has a space worthy of everything he’s overcome. That means everything to us.</p>",
  "quote": "\"He is an amazing, selfless child\"",
